<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9d9acba-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s421d"><num value="421d">§ 421d.</num><heading> Effect on existing laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as otherwise provided in sections 421a to 421h of this title, the provisions of the Federal reclamation laws, and Acts amendatory thereto, are continued in full force and effect.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9d9acbb-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1955-07-04/ch271/s4">July 4, 1955, ch. 271, § 4</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/69/245">69 Stat. 245</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/92/487">Pub. L. 92–487</ref>, <date date="1972-10-13">Oct. 13, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/805">86 Stat. 805</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9d9acbc-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc9d9acbd-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idc9d9acbe-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1972—<ref href="/us/pl/92/487">Pub. L. 92–487</ref> reenacted section without change.</p>
</note>
